                        <item>
                           <note xml:lang="en"><p>
<lb/>                                         The “Harkavy cards,” created by Avraham E. Harkavy</p><p>                              (1835–1919), were the foundation for his handwritten four-volume inventory</p><p>                              of the Yevr.-Arab. section of the Second Firkovitch Collection. This</p><p>                              inventory is today held at the Vernadsky National Library of Ukraine in</p><p>                              Kyiv, and also served as the basis of the library’s card catalog prepared</p><p>                              over the years by Harkavy himself, F. Kokovtzov, R. Ravrebe, A. Vasilev, and</p><p>                              V. Lebedev. </p><p>
<lb/>                                    </p></note>
                           <persName>Avraham Harkavy</persName>
                           <quote xml:lang="he"><p>
<lb/>                                        </p><p>                              מפי' דברים (ליפת; רשימת ההקדש<lb/>  </p><p>                           </p><p>
<lb/>                                    </p></quote>
